			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What Trade Skill Should a Bard be good at?<a name="69950"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 18 04 12:15 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>MHB's can take you all the way to 248. You can get the title &quot;Apprentice Brewer&quot; when you hit 100 and &quot;Journeyman Brewer&quot; when you hit 200. I never went to 250, but I think there's a title for that too. The first time you make it, you have to experiment. Once you get a successful combine, you've &quot;learned&quot; it and can add it to your favorite recipies list. The recipe is:
<br />

<br />
1 cask
<br />
3 malts
<br />
1 yeast
<br />
2 water flasks
<br />
2 short beers
<br />

<br />
2 bottles and a MHB is returned on success, 2 bottles and a cask is returned on failure.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866"> <img src="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/uf/Jiggidyjay/zingsig.jpg"></a></br><fontsize=8>Zingin Ansinging, Povar</fontsize></span></td>
