				<td colspan="2"><span>By pressing SHIFT+T you'll bring up a menu with all the titles you can have. These titles only show up before your name as people are looking at you, not in a /who. I have like 10 titles available to me. You can get titles available to you from hitting different skill levels of tradeskilling and different amounts of spent AA's. You can also get the &quot;Composer&quot; title by acquiring your epic 1.0. The only problem with that one is every time you die, the title poofs and you have to reapply it after you loot your SSS. You can change your titles at any time. So if you have a 120 in tailoring and a 220 in brewing, you can be an &quot;Apprentice tailor&quot; one minute and a &quot;Journeyman Brewer&quot; the next.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866"> <img src="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/uf/Jiggidyjay/zingsig.jpg"></a></br><fontsize=8>Zingin Ansinging, Povar</fontsize></span></td>
